article.headline: Toledo 71, N. Illinois 41
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Curtis Dennis scored 18 points and Toledo routed Northern Illinois 71-41 in a Mid-American Conference game Wednesday night to snap a three-game overall skid and a four-game losing streak in the series. The Rockets' winning margin was their largest over a MAC team since an 88-58 win over Eastern Michigan on Jan. 26, 2006. The Huskies' 41 points also were the fewest Toledo (9-9, 1-3) has allowed in a league game since beating Bowling Green 53-41 on Jan. 31, 1998. Northern Illinois (2-14, 1-3) stayed close early, with four ties and four lead changes. Toledo pulled ahead for good at 12-11 with 12:09 left until halftime, and built a 37-18 lead by intermission. Reese Holiday added 11 points and Dominique Buckley 10 for Toledo. The Huskies, coming off a 74-66 win over Central Michigan, had 23 turnovers and were led by Stian Berg and Keith Gray with eight points apiece.
